# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PII Detection Comparison Tool — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Azure AI Language — PII Detection (Cloud API) ────────────────────────────
# This is your Azure AI Language or Azure Cognitive Services resource.
# In the Azure Portal → your resource → Keys and Endpoint
# NOTE: This is labeled "Content Safety" in the UI but we use the
#       Text Analytics / AI Language PII endpoint from the same resource.
AZURE_CONTENT_SAFETY_KEY=your_azure_ai_language_key_here
AZURE_CONTENT_SAFETY_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource-name.cognitiveservices.azure.com

# ── Azure OpenAI (Optional — for future GPT-4o enrichment) ───────────────────
# Used if you want to add an LLM-based PII pass via Azure OpenAI GPT-4o
AZURE_OPENAI_KEY=your_azure_openai_key_here
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-aoai-resource.openai.azure.com
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o

# ── OpenAI Privacy Filter ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# No API key needed — model runs LOCALLY via HuggingFace transformers.
# First run will download ~2.8GB to ~/.cache/huggingface/
# Set a custom cache path if needed:
# HF_HOME=/path/to/your/hf_cache

# ── Microsoft Presidio ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# No API key needed — runs locally as a Python library.
# Requires spaCy model: python -m spacy download en_core_web_lg

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Install dependencies:
#    pip install -r requirements.txt
#
# 2. Download the spaCy NLP model (required for Presidio):
#    python -m spacy download en_core_web_lg
#
# 3. Copy this file and set your Azure credentials:
#    cp example.env .env
#    # Edit .env with your actual Azure keys
#
# 4. Run the server:
#    python main.py
#    # OR
#    uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
#
# 5. Open your browser:
#    http://localhost:8000
#
# 6. (Optional) Pre-load local models to avoid cold-start on first request:
#    Click "Warm Up Local Models" in the UI, or hit:
#    GET http://localhost:8000/api/warmup
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AZURE ENDPOINT NOTES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The app calls the Azure AI Language PII endpoint:
#   POST {endpoint}/text/analytics/v3.1/entities/recognition/pii
#
# This requires an Azure AI Language resource (NOT just Content Safety).
# If you have a multi-service Cognitive Services resource, it works for both.
#
# Pricing: https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/pricing/details/cognitive-services/language-service/
# Free tier: 5,000 transactions/month at no cost (F0 tier)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
